  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2003-10-21",
    "date": "2004-04-26T21:27:40Z",
    "text": "National Right-to-Work Act - Amends the National Labor Relations Act and the Railway Labor Act to repeal those provisions that permit employers, pursuant to a union security agreement, to require employees to join a union as a condition of employment (including provisions permitting railroad carriers to require, pursuant to such an agreement, payroll deduction of union dues or fees as a condition of employment)."
